<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968>
    bibo:endPage "54" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoosystematics and Evolution" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-01-12" ;
    bibo:startPage "21" ;
    bibo:volume "97" ;
    dc:creator "Gorin, Vladislav A.; Scherz, Mark D.; Korost, Dmitriy V.; Poyarkov, Nikolay A." ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Consequences of parallel miniaturisation in Microhylinae (Anura, Microhylidae), with the description of a new genus of diminutive South East Asian frogs" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure10>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure11>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure1> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Palmar views of hands (above) and thenar views of feet (below) of the representative Microhyla s. str. and Nanohyla gen. nov. species: N. annamensis (A, B), N. arboricola (C, D), M. minuta (E, F), and M. tetrix (G, H). Arrow indicates outer metatarsal tubercle. Not to scale. Line drawings by Valentina D. Kretova." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/496424" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure11>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Members of the new genus Nanohyla gen. nov. in life (males): N. annectens from Genting Highlands, Pahang, Malaysia (A), N. annamensis from Bidoup - Nui Ba N. P., Lam Dong, Vietnam (B), N. arboricola from Chu Yang Sin N. P., Dak Lak, Vietnam (C), N. hongiaoensis from Bidoup - Nui Ba N. P., Lam Dong, Vietnam (D), N. marmorata from Kon Chu Rang N. R., Gia Lai, Vietnam (E), N. nanapollexa from Kon Plong, Kon Tum, Vietnam (F), N. perparva from Gunung Mulu, Sarawak, Malaysia (G), N. petrigena from Gunung Mulu, Sarawak, Malaysia (H), and N. pulchella from Bidoup - Nui Ba N. P., Lam Dong, Vietnam (I). Insets show tympanic area of the each species; white arrow points at the tympanic rim of the external tympanum. Photos by Nikolay A. Poyarkov (A-S, D-F, I), Vu Dang Hoang Nguyen (D), and Indraneil Das (G, H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/496425" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.97.57968.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Distribution ranges of the three clades of the Microhyla - Glyphoglossus assemblage. Distribution area of Microhyla I is shown in yellow, of Microhyla II in red, and of Glyphoglossus in blue. Distributional data from Gorin et al. (2020). Question mark denotes the unconfirmed record of \" Microhyla annamensis \" from Khao Sebab in eastern Thailand by Taylor (1962)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/496415" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

